title.narrative: Strengthening Human Resources for Health (SHRH) - Capacity follow on

description.narrative: (Uganda): Strengthening Human Resources for Health (SHRH) is an award under the Capacity Plus Leader with Associate mechanism. It develops the capacities of the Government of Uganda's (GOU) central Ministries, districts, and professional councils to effectively and efficiently manage their human resources for health. Expected results in FY 2018 include: National HRH strategy updated, Community Health Extension Worker training rolled out, USG-supported staff transitioned to GOU payroll, mechanisms to reduce absenteeism fully rolled out, staffing norms at regional referral hospitals and lower-level facilities revised, and recruitment projection plan for Ministry of Health (MOH) updated. Interventions will include policy implementation, review of staffing norms and revision of schemes for health workers' services, technical assistance to MOH in strategic planning, recruitment, and performance management to contribute to overall improvement and sustainability in quality of service delivery and planning... ...
